    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "The dark side of pumpkin toadlet: a new species of Brachycephalus (Anura: Brachycephalidae) from Serra do Brigadeiro, southeastern Brazil" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570101>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570095>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570098>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570099>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570096>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570097>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570100>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570102> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570101>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Photos of Brachycephalus darkside sp. nov. in life: (A) female, (B) male, (C) same male hidden beneath roots, (D) roots where the male was found." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/570101/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570095>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Brachycephalus darkside sp. nov. holotype (MZUFV 16636, SVL 17.9 mm). (A) Dorsal and (B) ventral views of the body; (C) lateral view of the head; (D) palmar view of the hand and (E) plantar view of the foot. Scale bar = 3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/570095/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570098>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Histological analysis: (A) Dissected individual of Brachycephalus darkside sp. nov. (MZUFV 16579); (A 1) closer view of the dark tissue; (A 2) detail in the provision of pigmented tissue that follows adjacent muscle fibers. Transverse sections: (B) inclusion in resin; longitudinal section (C) inclusion in paraffin. Arrows indicate the dark pigments of connective tissue: epimysium (epm), perimysium (prm) and endomysium (edm). Muscle tissue (msc)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/570098/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570099>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Ventral and dorsal view of dissected preserved specimens of (A) Brachycephalus darkside sp. nov., showing the presence of dark tissue in the dorsal musculature, and (B) the absence of dark tissue in B. ephippium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/570099/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570096>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Cleared and double-stained specimen of Brachycephalus darkside sp. nov. (paratype MZUFV 15566, SVL 16.14 mm, adult). Dorsal (A) and lateral (B) view of the skull; dorsal (C) and ventral (D) views of the skull, vertebrae and para-axial bony plates. Legends: exoc (exoccipital), fp (frontoparietal), max (maxilla), nas (nasal), owin (oval window), pmax (premaxilla), ppl (parotic plate), prsph (parasphenoid), ptr (pterigoid), PV (pressacral vertebrae), pvpl (paravertebral plate), sac (sacrum), sq (squamosal), SPl (spinal plate), sphen (sphenethmoid), uro (urostyle), vm (vomer)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/570096/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570097>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Brachycephalus darkside sp. nov., (A) dorsal view of right hand, dorsal view of right foot, and (C) ventral view of pectoral girdle with scapula and supra-scapula deflected." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/570097/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570100>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Spectrogram (above) and oscillogram (bellow) of the calls of Brachycephalus darkside sp. nov. (A) Sequence of four notes of the advertisement call, recorded on 20 November 2015, 12 h 40, air temperature 22 ° C, paratype MZUFV 16629. (B) Sequence of six notes of the aggressive call, recorded on 17 December 2015, 19 h 00, air temperature 19 ° C, holotype MZUFV 16636." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/570100/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.570102>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Geographical distribution of Brachycephalus darkside sp. nov., and of Brachycephalus didactylus, B. pernix and B. ephippium species groups. BA (Bahia State), MG (Minas Gerais State), ES (Espírito Santo State), RJ (Rio de Janeiro State), SP (São Paulo State), PR (Paraná State), SC (Santa Catarina State)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/570102/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

